    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It's not a wonderful solution, but a known workaround is to delete the app's data folder (`~/Library/Application Support/Status` on macOS) then start over by re-importing your seed phrase.\r\n\r\nThe older/larger the data folder is (particularly the sqlcipher database created by status-go), the slower the app performs. With a fresh data folder and a build of latest `master` you'll notice a *dramatic* difference.\r\n\r\nWe're researching what the problem is with older/larger data folders, but it's not clear yet.",
