    "updated_at": "2021-07-29T20:34:28Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "We found the likely cause for this is getting the contact list from `wakuext_contacts` which is done [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/blob/master/src/status/libstatus/contacts.nim#L26). It seems each time we switch channels (and other actions like switching communities etc..) this is called. This is not just the list of contacts but all the list of 'seen' contacts, it's usually pretty light or small enough to not be noticeable even with lots of channels and history fetching. however if someone uses the app for a long time (maybe months even) as this gets bigger and bigger it starts to impact the performance noticeably.\r\n\r\nAs a fix we need to improve the cache, be smarter on what we return and how etc.. (under discussion)",
